  <section class="page-hero post-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="post-wrap">
        <nav class="crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/en/">Home</a>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
          <a href="/en/blog/">Blog</a>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
          <span>Employer Branding Video: How to Attract the Right Talent</span>
        </nav>
        <span class="eyebrow">Employer Branding</span>
        <h1>Employer Branding Video: How to Attract the Right Talent</h1>
        <p class="lead">In today's job market, companies aren't the only ones choosing — top candidates are choosing too. An employer branding film is the most powerful way to show them why they should choose you.</p>
        <p class="post-meta"><span>Viven Team</span> <span>·</span> <span>July 21, 2026</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec" style="padding-top:40px">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
      <img src="https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/1996945412-11440cd0df3521e998bff13bcaab8bbed2a405430e442c73f998df74099d28b2-d_960?region=us" alt="Employer Branding Video: How to Attract the Right Talent" loading="eager" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin:8px 0 26px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover" />

      <h2>Show your real culture, not stock footage</h2>
      <p>The most common employer branding mistake is looking like everyone else: generic imagery, stock-photo smiles, empty phrases. The talent you actually want to attract spots that instantly. A good film shows your real people, your real spaces, your real way of working. Authenticity is what makes it land.</p>

      <h2>Attract the right people, not everyone</h2>
      <p>A good employer branding video isn't trying to appeal to everyone — it's trying to resonate with the right people, and filter out the ones who wouldn't be a fit along the way. That lowers cost-per-hire and improves the quality of the candidates who apply.</p>

      <h2>Where an employer branding film lives</h2>
      <p>These films work on several fronts at once:</p>
      <ul>
      <li>On your <strong>careers page</strong>, where they turn visitors into applicants.</li>
      <li>On <strong>LinkedIn</strong> and job ads, where they boost response rates.</li>
      <li>In the hiring process, where they help candidates fall for the company before the interview.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Brands already doing this</h2>
      <p>We've produced employer branding films for UBS, Siemens and KPMG that attract exactly the candidate profile they're looking for. The key is always the same: a real story, told with real filmmaking craft.</p>

      <p>Learn more about our <a href="/en/services/employer-branding/">employer branding</a> work, or <a href="/en/contact/">tell us what talent you want to attract</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- ============ RELATED ============ -->
<section class="sec" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="related reveal">
      <h2>Related reading</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
      {related.map((r) => (
        <a href={'/en/blog/' + r.slug + '/'} class="related-card reveal">
